Posts.Content: Has anyone ever been diagnosed with this rare breast cancer?  I was told I'm the 36th in the world to get this rare cancer. Not much info on the internet to research.  I do know I have the Low-Grade which is the better one although the recurrance rate is 30%.
Posts.Title: Adneosquamous Breast Cancer

Posts.Content: I'm post lumpectomy for breast cancer.  Had 32 radiation treatments.   I'm now experiencing tingling that affects my entire left side all the way through my back.   It started about 2 months after radiation and seems to be getting worse.  It appears to be worse at night and has started to happen during the day.   There's also a burning feeling in my back.  Could this be from the radiation and if so does anyone else have this?
Posts.Title: Post Radiation 'tingling' on entire left side
